        <div n="235-37L1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">B<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ENEATH</hi></hi> this verdant hillock lies<hi rend="underline">Demar</hi>, the wealthy and the wise.<gap/><gap/></l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-2"> His heirs, that he might safely rest,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-3"> Have put his carcass in a chest:</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-4"> The very chest, in which, they say,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-5"> His other self, his money, lay.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-6"> And if his heirs continue kind</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-7"> To that dear self he left behind,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-8"> I dare believe, that four in five</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-235-37L1-line-9"> Will think his better half alive.235-37L1   </l></lg></div>
